[StalVars]: In my case, I also observed that 'set_detect_anomaly(True)' makes the forward pass much slower.

---

[soulitzer]: That is expected @StalVars 

See the warning in https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/autograd.html#anomaly-detection

The performance hit is because on the creation of every node of the backward graph extra metadata, e.g. current stack trace of the forward execution is stored.
